      ["What is a chart of accounts?", "A list of all accounts used by a business, organized by type and purpose."],
      ["Why create a chart of accounts?", "To organize accounts for recording and reporting financial transactions efficiently."],
      ["Which account types are included in a chart of accounts?", "Assets, liabilities, owner’s equity, revenues, and expenses."],
      ["Scenario: A business starts a new department. What should be updated in the chart of accounts?", "Add new accounts relevant to the department’s operations."],
      ["How are accounts usually numbered in a chart of accounts?", "Using a coding system that groups accounts by type."],
      ["Scenario: New equipment is purchased. What chart of accounts action is needed?", "Add an Equipment account if it doesn’t exist."],
      ["Why is consistency important in numbering accounts?", "It helps track and classify transactions accurately."],
      ["Scenario: A company adds a new revenue stream. How is the chart of accounts updated?", "Add a new revenue account for the stream."],
      ["What is a current asset account?", "An asset expected to be used or converted to cash within one year."],
      ["What is a long-term liability account?", "A liability due more than one year in the future."],
      ["Scenario: The business opens a new bank account. Which chart of accounts update is needed?", "Add a Cash or Bank account if needed."],
      ["What is the role of account descriptions in a chart of accounts?", "They clarify the purpose and usage of each account."],
      ["Scenario: A new office supply category is needed. How is the chart updated?", "Add a Supplies Expense or Supplies Asset account as appropriate."],
      ["What is the advantage of organizing accounts by type?", "It simplifies financial reporting and analysis."],
      ["Scenario: Business starts selling online. What chart of accounts update is required?", "Add a Sales Revenue account for online sales."],
      ["Why should accounts be reviewed periodically?", "To ensure they reflect current business operations and needs."],
      ["Scenario: A liability is paid off completely. What chart of accounts action is needed?", "No new account is needed; update balances accordingly."],
      ["How does a chart of accounts support journalizing?", "It provides a reference for selecting correct accounts for transactions."],
      ["What is the difference between a master and subsidiary chart of accounts?", "The master contains all accounts; subsidiary tracks detailed balances."],
      ["Scenario: Owner invests personal funds into the business. Which account should be used?", "Capital account in the chart of accounts."],
      ["Why is numbering ranges assigned to account types?", "To group similar accounts and facilitate reporting."],
      ["Scenario: A business starts offering a new service. How should the chart of accounts change?", "Add a service revenue account to track income."],
      ["How do expense accounts appear in a chart of accounts?", "Grouped together under expense category with descriptive names."],
      ["Scenario: Prepaid insurance is purchased. What account is needed?", "Prepaid Insurance as an asset account."],
      ["What is the consequence of not updating a chart of accounts?", "Transactions may be misclassified, leading to inaccurate financial reports."],
      ["How should accounts be named for clarity?", "Use descriptive names that reflect their purpose and content."],
      ["Scenario: Business acquires new long-term debt. Which account is updated?", "Add a Notes Payable or Long-Term Liability account."],
      ["Why is a chart of accounts important for FBLA exams?", "It tests understanding of account classification and organization."],
      ["Scenario: Owner withdraws cash. Which account is used?", "Drawing account under owner’s equity."],
      ["What is a contra-account in a chart of accounts?", "An account that offsets another, such as Accumulated Depreciation against Equipment."],
      ["Scenario: Depreciation is recorded. Which account is updated?", "Accumulated Depreciation contra-asset account."],
      ["Why group accounts logically in the chart?", "It improves efficiency in posting and reporting transactions."],
      ["Scenario: A business adds a new utility. How should the chart change?", "Add a Utilities Expense account for that service."],
      ["How are income statement accounts represented in the chart?", "As revenue and expense accounts, grouped by type."],
      ["How are balance sheet accounts represented in the chart?", "As asset, liability, and owner’s equity accounts."],
      ["What skill is tested by creating and updating a chart of accounts?", "Proper account classification and adapting to business needs."]

