      ["What is the basic accounting equation?", "Assets = Liabilities + Owner’s Equity."],
      ["Why is the accounting equation important?", "It ensures the balance sheet remains balanced and reflects financial position."],
      ["Scenario: Owner invests $5,000 cash. How does the equation change?", "Assets increase by $5,000, Owner’s Equity increases by $5,000."],
      ["Scenario: Business borrows $2,000 from a bank. How does the equation change?", "Assets increase by $2,000 (Cash), Liabilities increase by $2,000 (Notes Payable)."],
      ["Scenario: Purchase equipment for $3,000 cash. How does the equation change?", "Equipment (asset) increases by $3,000, Cash (asset) decreases by $3,000; equation remains balanced."],
      ["Scenario: Business pays $500 rent. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) decrease by $500, Owner’s Equity (Expenses) decrease by $500."],
      ["Scenario: Earn $1,200 revenue on account. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Accounts Receivable) increase by $1,200, Owner’s Equity (Revenue) increases by $1,200."],
      ["Scenario: Owner withdraws $400 for personal use. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) decrease by $400, Owner’s Equity (Drawing) decreases by $400."],
      ["Scenario: Pay $600 to supplier for accounts payable. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) decrease $600, Liabilities (Accounts Payable) decrease $600."],
      ["What happens when a business incurs an expense on account?", "Liabilities increase, Owner’s Equity decreases; equation remains balanced."],
      ["Scenario: Purchase supplies on credit for $250. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Supplies) increase $250, Liabilities (Accounts Payable) increase $250."],
      ["Scenario: Receive cash from a customer previously on account. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) increase, Assets (Accounts Receivable) decrease; equation stays balanced."],
      ["How do liabilities affect the accounting equation?", "Liabilities represent claims on assets by creditors, increasing total obligations."],
      ["How does owner’s equity affect the accounting equation?", "Represents residual claims of owner; increases with investment or net income, decreases with withdrawals or losses."],
      ["Scenario: Business pays $200 for utilities previously owed. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) decrease $200, Liabilities (Utilities Payable) decrease $200."],
      ["Scenario: Owner invests additional $1,000 cash. How does the equation change?", "Assets increase $1,000, Owner’s Equity increases $1,000."],
      ["Scenario: Business earns $800 revenue paid in cash. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) increase $800, Owner’s Equity (Revenue) increases $800."],
      ["Scenario: Business purchases $500 of supplies for cash. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Supplies) increase $500, Assets (Cash) decrease $500; net effect on total assets is zero."],
      ["Scenario: Business repays part of a long-term loan $1,500. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) decrease $1,500, Liabilities (Loan Payable) decrease $1,500."],
      ["How does revenue affect the accounting equation?", "Increases Owner’s Equity through retained earnings or capital."],
      ["How does an expense affect the accounting equation?", "Decreases Owner’s Equity."],
      ["Scenario: Business receives a $300 advance from a customer. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) increase $300, Liabilities (Unearned Revenue) increase $300."],
      ["Scenario: Business purchases equipment for $2,000, half cash and half on account. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Equipment) +$2,000, Assets (Cash) -$1,000, Liabilities (Accounts Payable) +$1,000."],
      ["Scenario: Owner withdraws $600 and revenue was $2,000. How does equity change?", "Revenue increases Owner’s Equity $2,000, Drawing decreases $600; net increase $1,400."],
      ["Why must total assets always equal total liabilities plus equity?", "To ensure the accounting equation is balanced and financial statements are accurate."],
      ["Scenario: Business receives a loan of $5,000 and invests $2,000 cash. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) +$7,000, Liabilities +$5,000, Owner’s Equity +$2,000."],
      ["Scenario: Business earns $1,500 revenue on account, pays $500 expenses. Net effect on equity?", "Revenue increases Owner’s Equity $1,500, Expenses decrease $500; net increase $1,000."],
      ["Scenario: Business purchases inventory $1,200 cash. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Inventory) +$1,200, Assets (Cash) -$1,200; total assets unchanged."],
      ["Scenario: Owner invests land worth $10,000. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Land) +$10,000, Owner’s Equity +$10,000."],
      ["Scenario: Business issues $3,000 in short-term notes payable. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) +$3,000, Liabilities (Notes Payable) +$3,000."],
      ["Scenario: Pay $700 of previously incurred accounts payable. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) -$700, Liabilities (Accounts Payable) -$700."],
      ["Scenario: Receive cash from customer on account $500. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) +$500, Assets (Accounts Receivable) -$500; total assets unchanged."],
      ["How can you check if the accounting equation is applied correctly?", "Verify that Assets equal Liabilities plus Owner’s Equity after each transaction."],
      ["Scenario: Business pays $200 expense in cash. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Cash) -$200, Owner’s Equity (Expense) -$200."],
      ["Scenario: Purchase equipment $4,000 with $1,000 cash and $3,000 on account. How does the equation change?", "Assets (Equipment) +$4,000, Assets (Cash) -$1,000, Liabilities +$3,000; equation remains balanced."]
