      ["What is an income statement?", "A financial statement showing a company's revenues, expenses, and net income or loss over a specific period."],
      ["What is the main purpose of an income statement?", "To report the results of operations and measure profitability for a period."],
      ["Scenario: Company earns $50,000 in sales and incurs $30,000 in expenses. Net income?", "$20,000."],
      ["What is the first step in preparing an income statement?", "List all revenue sources for the reporting period."],
      ["What is the second step in preparing an income statement?", "List all expenses incurred during the same period."],
      ["Scenario: Revenue $40,000, Expenses $45,000. Net result?", "Net loss of $5,000."],
      ["What is gross profit?", "Revenue minus cost of goods sold (COGS)."],
      ["Scenario: Revenue $20,000, COGS $12,000. Gross profit?", "$8,000."],
      ["What are operating expenses?", "Expenses related to normal business operations, such as salaries and rent."],
      ["Scenario: Gross profit $15,000, Operating expenses $5,000. Operating income?", "$10,000."],
      ["What are non-operating items?", "Gains or losses not related to core operations, like interest or asset sales."],
      ["Scenario: Company earns $500 interest. Where does it appear?", "As a non-operating item on the income statement."],
      ["What is net income?", "The excess of total revenues over total expenses."],
      ["Scenario: Revenue $60,000, Total expenses $50,000. Net income?", "$10,000."],
      ["What is net loss?", "When total expenses exceed total revenues."],
      ["Scenario: Revenue $30,000, Expenses $35,000. Net result?", "Net loss of $5,000."],
      ["What is the difference between a single-step and multi-step income statement?", "Single-step summarizes revenues and expenses in one step; multi-step separates operating, non-operating, and other items."],
      ["Scenario: Company separates sales, COGS, operating expenses, and interest. Statement type?", "Multi-step income statement."],
      ["Why is the income statement important for investors?", "It shows profitability and efficiency, helping assess company performance."],
      ["Scenario: Manager compares last quarter’s net income to this quarter. Purpose?", "Evaluate trends in profitability and operational efficiency."],
      ["What is the reporting period on an income statement?", "The specific time span, such as monthly, quarterly, or annually, covered by the statement."],
      ["Scenario: Company wants to see March’s performance. Which statement?", "Monthly income statement."],
      ["How does net income affect the balance sheet?", "It increases retained earnings in the equity section of the balance sheet."],
      ["Scenario: Net income $8,000. Balance sheet effect?", "Retained earnings increase by $8,000."],
      ["What is the role of the matching principle in income statement preparation?", "Expenses are recorded in the same period as the revenues they helped generate."],
      ["Scenario: Supplies purchased in March used in April. When expense recorded?", "April, according to the matching principle."],
      ["What are non-operating gains and losses?", "Revenues or expenses unrelated to core business operations, such as selling old equipment."],
      ["Scenario: Company sells old equipment for $1,000 more than book value. Entry?", "Non-operating gain of $1,000."],
      ["Why is separating operating and non-operating items helpful?", "It clarifies core business performance from incidental gains or losses."],
      ["Scenario: Company earns $2,000 from sales and $500 from interest. Expenses $1,500. Net income?", "$1,000."],
      ["What is the importance of showing gross profit on an income statement?", "It measures profitability from core product sales before operating expenses."],
      ["Scenario: Revenue $25,000, COGS $10,000, Operating expenses $8,000. Net income?", "$7,000."],
      ["How does the income statement help in decision-making?", "It identifies profitable areas and highlights costs needing control."],
      ["Scenario: Manager sees high operating expenses. Action?", "Reduce costs or improve operational efficiency."],
      ["What is earnings per share (EPS) on the income statement?", "Net income divided by outstanding shares, showing profit per share."],
      ["Scenario: Net income $50,000, 10,000 shares. EPS?", "$5 per share."],
      ["Why is accuracy important when preparing an income statement?", "Errors can misrepresent profitability, affecting decisions by investors and management."]
