      ["Scenario: Sarah opens a small bakery alone. Type of ownership?", "Sole proprietorship."],
      ["What is unlimited liability?", "The owner is personally responsible for all debts and obligations of the business."],
      ["Scenario: Owner’s business owes $50,000. Personal assets at risk?", "Yes, due to unlimited liability."],
      ["How are profits taxed in a sole proprietorship?", "Profits are taxed once on the owner’s personal income tax return."],
      ["Scenario: Bakery earns $30,000 profit. How is it taxed?", "The $30,000 is reported on the owner’s personal tax return."],
      ["What is the management structure?", "The owner has full control over all decisions and operations of the business."],
      ["Scenario: Owner decides to expand menu options. Who approves?", "The owner alone, as sole manager."],
      ["What is the advantage regarding startup?", "Sole proprietorships are easy and inexpensive to establish with minimal legal formalities."],
      ["Scenario: Owner opens business next week with minimal paperwork. Advantage?", "Quick and simple startup."],
      ["What is the disadvantage related to continuity?", "The business may end if the owner dies, retires, or leaves without succession planning."],
      ["Scenario: Owner dies unexpectedly. What happens to the business?", "The business may dissolve unless a succession plan exists."],
      ["What is an advantage of decision-making?", "Decisions are made quickly since the owner does not need approval from partners or a board."],
      ["Scenario: Owner changes pricing strategy immediately. Benefit?", "Fast decision-making without delays."],
      ["Why is personal responsibility both an advantage and disadvantage?", "Owner keeps all profits but also bears full risk for debts and losses."]
