      ["Corporation", "A legal entity separate from its owners that can own assets, incur liabilities, and issue stock."],
      ["Formation of a Corporation", "The process of legally creating a corporation including filing articles of incorporation and issuing stock."],
      ["Stockholder", "An individual or entity that owns shares in a corporation and has a claim on its assets and earnings."],
      ["Common Stock", "Equity issued to owners representing their ownership in a corporation, typically with voting rights."],
      ["Preferred Stock", "Stock that provides owners preferential treatment for dividends and asset distribution, usually without voting rights."],
      ["Dividends", "Portions of a corporation’s earnings distributed to stockholders as a return on investment."],
      ["Retained Earnings", "The cumulative net income of a corporation that is retained rather than distributed as dividends."],
      ["Revenue Account", "An account that records income earned from business operations, increasing equity."],
      ["Expense Account", "An account that records costs incurred in the process of earning revenue, decreasing equity."],
      ["Drawing Account", "An account used by sole proprietors or partners to track withdrawals of business funds for personal use."],
      ["Capital Account", "An account representing the owner’s interest in a business, increased by investments and net income, decreased by withdrawals."],
      ["Allocation of Earnings", "The process of distributing net income to stockholders or retained earnings based on ownership or policy."],
      ["Distribution of Earnings", "Payment of dividends or other forms of income allocation to stockholders."],
      ["Dissolution of a Corporation", "The formal process of closing a corporation, paying liabilities, and distributing remaining assets to stockholders."],
      ["Journal Entry", "A record of a business transaction in accounting, showing debits and credits."],
      ["Debit", "An entry that increases assets or expenses or decreases liabilities, equity, or revenue."],
      ["Credit", "An entry that increases liabilities, equity, or revenue or decreases assets or expenses."],
      ["Balance Sheet", "A financial statement showing a corporation's assets, liabilities, and equity at a specific point in time."],
      ["Income Statement", "A financial statement summarizing revenues, expenses, and net income over a period."],
      ["Closing Entries", "Journal entries made at the end of an accounting period to transfer balances of temporary accounts to permanent accounts."],
      ["Temporary Accounts", "Accounts such as revenue, expense, and drawing that are closed at the end of an accounting period."],
      ["Permanent Accounts", "Accounts that carry their balances into future accounting periods, such as capital and asset accounts."],
      ["Net Income", "The excess of revenues over expenses, increasing owner’s equity."],
      ["Net Loss", "The excess of expenses over revenues, decreasing owner’s equity."],
      ["Stock Dividend", "A dividend paid in additional shares of stock rather than cash."],
      ["Stock Split", "An increase in the number of shares outstanding with a proportional decrease in the par value per share."],
      ["Par Value", "The nominal value of a share of stock assigned in the corporate charter."],
      ["Additional Paid-In Capital", "The amount paid by stockholders above the par value of the stock."],
      ["Treasury Stock", "Shares that were issued and later reacquired by the corporation, reducing equity."],
      ["Example: Dividend Payment", "If a corporation declares $1 per share dividend on 1,000 shares, stockholders receive $1,000 total."],
      ["Example: Revenue Entry", "A company earns $500 in sales; Revenue account is credited $500, increasing equity."],
      ["Example: Expense Entry", "A company pays $200 for utilities; Expense account is debited $200, reducing equity."],
      ["Example: Drawing Withdrawal", "Owner withdraws $100 for personal use; Drawing account is debited $100, reducing capital."],
      ["Example: Retained Earnings Increase", "Net income of $1,000 increases retained earnings and equity."],
      ["Example: Stock Issuance", "Corporation issues 100 shares at $10 par; Cash debited $1,000, Common Stock credited $1,000."],
      ["Example: Corporation Dissolution", "Assets are sold, liabilities paid, remaining $5,000 distributed to stockholders."],
      ["Example: Stock Split", "2-for-1 stock split doubles shares from 100 to 200 and halves par value from $10 to $5."],
      ["Effect of Revenue on Equity", "Revenue increases net income, which increases retained earnings and overall equity."],
      ["Effect of Expenses on Equity", "Expenses reduce net income, which decreases retained earnings and equity."],
      ["Effect of Drawings on Equity", "Withdrawals reduce the capital account, decreasing owner’s equity."],
      ["Revenue Recognition Principle", "Revenue is recognized when earned, regardless of when cash is received."],
      ["Matching Principle", "Expenses are recorded in the same period as the revenues they helped generate."],
      ["Example: Allocation of Net Income", "Corporation earns $10,000; $7,000 retained, $3,000 distributed as dividends."],
      ["Example: Preferred Dividend", "Preferred stockholders receive $500 dividends before common stockholders."],
      ["Example: Journal Entry for Expenses", "Debit Rent Expense $500; Credit Cash $500."],
      ["Example: Closing Revenue Account", "Revenue account of $2,000 is closed to Retained Earnings; Debit Revenue $2,000, Credit Retained Earnings $2,000."],
      ["Example: Closing Expense Account", "Expense account of $1,200 is closed to Retained Earnings; Debit Retained Earnings $1,200, Credit Expenses $1,200."],
      ["Example: Journal Entry for Dividend", "Declared $300 dividend; Debit Retained Earnings $300, Credit Dividends Payable $300."],
      ["Example: Effects of Net Loss", "Company has $500 loss; Retained Earnings reduced by $500, decreasing equity."],
      ["Example: Additional Paid-In Capital Entry", "Stock sold for $15 with $10 par; Debit Cash $15, Credit Common Stock $10, Credit Additional Paid-In Capital $5."],
      ["Example: Treasury Stock Purchase", "Company buys back 50 shares at $12; Debit Treasury Stock $600, Credit Cash $600."],
      ["Example: Effect of Stock Dividend", "10% stock dividend issued on 1,000 shares increases shares to 1,100; reduces retained earnings proportionally."],
      ["Example: Closing Drawing Account", "Owner’s drawing of $400 is closed; Debit Capital $400, Credit Drawing $400."],
      ["Example: Effect of Issuing Preferred Stock", "Issue 100 preferred shares at $20; Cash debited $2,000, Preferred Stock credited $2,000."],
      ["Example: Recording Net Income", "Net income of $2,500 increases Retained Earnings, boosting equity."],
      ["Example: Recording Net Loss", "Net loss of $800 decreases Retained Earnings, reducing equity."]
