      ["Credit Terms", "The terms set by a supplier for payment on account, such as 2/10, n/30."],
      ["Example: Purchases on Account Entry", "Debit Inventory $1,000, Credit Accounts Payable $1,000."],
      ["Example: Purchase Return Entry", "Debit Accounts Payable $200, Credit Inventory $200."],
      ["Example: Purchase Allowance Entry", "Debit Accounts Payable $150, Credit Inventory $150."],
      ["Example: Purchase Discount Entry", "Debit Accounts Payable $1,000, Credit Cash $980, Credit Inventory $20."],
      ["Example: Posting to Accounts Payable Ledger", "Record purchase on account $1,000 to supplier’s individual account."],
      ["Example: Schedule of Accounts Payable", "Supplier A $500, Supplier B $1,000; total $1,500 equals control account."],
      ["Example: Direct Write-Off Entry", "Customer $200 uncollectible; Debit Bad Debt Expense $200, Credit Accounts Receivable $200."],
      ["Example: Allowance Method Entry", "Estimate 2% of receivables $10,000; Debit Bad Debt Expense $200, Credit Allowance for Doubtful Accounts $200."],
      ["Example: Writing Off Allowance Method", "Customer $300 uncollectible; Debit Allowance for Doubtful Accounts $300, Credit Accounts Receivable $300."],
      ["Example: Recovering Written-Off Account", "Debit Accounts Receivable $200, Credit Allowance $200; then Debit Cash $200, Credit Accounts Receivable $200."],
      ["Example: Net Purchases Calculation", "Purchases $5,000 - Returns $500 - Discounts $200 = Net Purchases $4,300."],
      ["Example: Posting Payment to Supplier", "Pay $1,000; Debit Accounts Payable $1,000, Credit Cash $1,000."],
      ["Example: Subsidiary Ledger Verification", "Total individual supplier balances $2,500 match general ledger control account $2,500."],
      ["Example: Recognizing Bad Debt Expense", "Estimate $500 uncollectible; Debit Bad Debt Expense $500, Credit Allowance $500."],
      ["Example: Adjusting Entry for Allowance", "End-of-period estimate of doubtful accounts recorded to match revenues and expenses."],
      ["Example: Recording Credit Terms Payment", "Invoice $1,000, terms 2/10, n/30; payment within 10 days: Debit Accounts Payable $1,000, Credit Cash $980, Credit Inventory $20."],
      ["Example: Purchase Entry with Freight", "Debit Inventory $1,050, Credit Accounts Payable $1,050 including $50 freight-in."],
      ["Example: Direct Write-Off Timing", "Bad debt recorded only when account is confirmed uncollectible."],
      ["Example: Allowance Method Matching Principle", "Estimates bad debts in same period as revenue recognition."],
      ["Example: Posting Multiple Supplier Payments", "Pay $500 to Supplier A, $300 to Supplier B; update subsidiary ledger and control account."],
      ["Example: Writing Off Small Balance", "Customer $50 uncollectible; Debit Bad Debt Expense $50, Credit Accounts Receivable $50."],
      ["Example: Recovering Previously Written-Off Account", "Customer pays $50; reverse write-off and record cash collection."],
      ["Example: End-of-Month Subsidiary Ledger Check", "Ensure all supplier balances sum to Accounts Payable control account."],
      ["Example: Net Purchases for Period", "Purchases $10,000, returns $1,000, discounts $500; net purchases $8,500."],
      ["Example: Recording Partial Payment", "Pay $400 of $1,000 owed; Debit Accounts Payable $400, Credit Cash $400."],
      ["Example: Allowance Method Estimation Update", "Adjust Allowance account based on new period-end receivable balances."],
      ["Example: Direct Write-Off vs Allowance", "Direct write-off may distort net income timing; allowance better matches expense to revenue."],
      ["Example: Schedule Preparation for Audit", "Prepare schedule of accounts payable to verify accuracy before audit."],
      ["Example: Recognizing Purchase Discounts Taken", "Early payment discount reduces cost of inventory and cash paid."],
      ["Example: Recording Returned Inventory", "Adjust both Accounts Payable and Inventory for returned merchandise."],
      ["Example: Writing Off Large Uncollectible Account", "Debit Bad Debt Expense $2,000, Credit Accounts Receivable $2,000."],
      ["Example: Allowance Method Year-End Adjustment", "Increase allowance to $1,000; Debit Bad Debt Expense $300, Credit Allowance $300."],
      ["Example: Posting Purchase Journal Entries", "All purchase entries transferred to supplier accounts in subsidiary ledger."],
      ["Example: Reconciling Subsidiary Ledger", "Confirm totals of supplier balances match Accounts Payable control account before financial statement preparation."],
      ["Example: Uncollectible Accounts Recovery", "Previously written-off account paid; Debit Accounts Receivable $500, Credit Allowance $500; then Debit Cash $500, Credit Accounts Receivable $500."],
      ["Example: Differential Impact on Net Purchases", "Purchase returns and discounts reduce net purchases, affecting inventory valuation and cost of goods sold."]
